Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), indicating possible renal dysfunction and/or dehydration. Hemoglobin A1c is low, which may reflect anemia or recent changes in glycemic control. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, hydration status, and possible underlying metabolic or systemic conditions.
